# Video & media conventions

Product Switcher supports **video scrub mode** (wheel maps to `video.currentTime`) or **color fallback mode** (`VIDEO_SRC = null`).

## VIDEO_SRC configuration

- Defined in `scripts/main.js`: `var VIDEO_SRC = null;`
- Patched by `setup-video.sh` after FFmpeg pipeline — **not** in index.html.
- Relative path from project root, e.g. `'assets/product.mp4'`.

## Server requirements

| Server | Range requests | Video seeking |
|--------|----------------|---------------|
| `npm run dev` (`serve`) | ✅ | Works |
| `python -m http.server` | ❌ | **Broken** — do not use for video QA |

Always document this when adding dev instructions.

## FFmpeg pipeline (`setup-video.sh`)

1. Scan `assets/` for first `.mp4` / `.mov`.
2. Convert `.mov` → H.264 `.mp4` (`libx264`, `yuv420p`, no audio).
3. Extract 3 thumb frames at duration/6, duration/2, 5×duration/6 → `nav-icon-1..3.png`.
4. Patch `VIDEO_SRC` in `scripts/main.js`.

Manual commands (also in index.html comment block):

```bash
ffmpeg -i assets/YOUR_VIDEO.mov -c:v libx264 -preset fast -crf 23 -pix_fmt yuv420p -an assets/product.mp4

DURATION=$(ffprobe -v error -show_entries format=duration -of csv=p=0 assets/product.mp4)
T1=$(echo "$DURATION / 6" | bc -l)
T2=$(echo "$DURATION / 2" | bc -l)
T3=$(echo "$DURATION * 5 / 6" | bc -l)
ffmpeg -ss "$T1" -i assets/product.mp4 -frames:v 1 -q:v 2 assets/nav-icon-1.png
# ... T2, T3 for nav-icon-2, nav-icon-3
```

Frame times must align with section midpoints: `(index + 0.5) / SECTION_COUNT`.

## Color fallback

- `SECTION_COLORS`: `#C4A882`, `#C0C0C0`, `#D4C876` — sync with switcher thumbs.
- `progressToColor()` lerps between adjacent colors by scroll progress.
- `.fallback-color` injected into `#centralArea` with `aria-hidden="true"`.

## Video element setup

```javascript
videoEl.muted = true;
videoEl.playsInline = true;
videoEl.preload = 'auto';
// RAF: videoEl.currentTime = scrollProgress * videoEl.duration;
```

- No autoplay with sound.
- 8s metadata timeout → fallback mode if load fails.
- On error: remove video element, init fallback, do not leave broken `<video>`.

## Switcher thumbs in video mode

- `backgroundImage: url('assets/nav-icon-N.png')` on `.switcher__inner`.
- `backgroundColor` still set from `SECTION_COLORS` as fallback if PNG missing.

## ScrollTrigger (optional — not loaded)

Current scrub uses RAF + native `currentTime`, not GSAP ScrollTrigger. If adding scroll-linked GSAP effects later:

```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/gsap@3.12.7/dist/ScrollTrigger.min.js"></script>
<script>gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);</script>
```

Only add when a feature requires it — see README "Optional: ScrollTrigger".
